Subject: VisAttributes: force runtime strlen() on GEOMODEL_INSTALL_PREFIX

VP1GeometrySystems/src/VisAttributes.cxx builds the gmex share-dir path
in three places via:

    const char * installPath = GEOMODEL_INSTALL_PREFIX;
    std::string installedShare = installPath + std::string("/share/gmex/");

GEOMODEL_INSTALL_PREFIX is a -D string literal baked in at CMake time.
On conda-forge it is padded to a fixed length (~210 bytes) so that
rattler-build's binary prefix replacement can swap in any shorter
runtime prefix; the unused tail bytes become NUL.

Because `installPath` is a `const char *` to a literal whose length GCC
constant-folds, `char_traits::length(installPath)` returns the
compile-time literal size (~210), not strlen() of the relocated string.
The std::string therefore copies the embedded NULs. Passing
`installedShare.c_str()` to std::ifstream truncates at the first NUL,
so gmex opens the env prefix directory itself, libstdc++ throws
"basic_filebuf::underflow error reading the file: Is a directory" from
a Qt timer event, and gmex aborts before any geometry can be loaded.

Constructing `std::string(GEOMODEL_INSTALL_PREFIX)` explicitly invokes
the const-char* string constructor, which uses a runtime strlen that
stops at the first NUL. Three identical fixes.

--- a/GeoModelVisualization/VP1GeometrySystems/src/VisAttributes.cxx
+++ b/GeoModelVisualization/VP1GeometrySystems/src/VisAttributes.cxx
@@ -295,8 +295,7 @@
   if (gxShareDir) locations.insert(locations.begin(), gxShareDir+std::string("/"));
   // Add 4)
   //const char * installPath = STR_NAME( GEOMODEL_INSTALL_PREFIX ); // old CMake setup
-  const char * installPath = GEOMODEL_INSTALL_PREFIX; // new CMake setup
-  std::string installedShare = installPath + std::string("/share/gmex/");
+  std::string installedShare = std::string(GEOMODEL_INSTALL_PREFIX) + "/share/gmex/";
   locations.push_back(installedShare);
   // Add 5) and 6)
   locations.push_back("/usr/local/share/gmex/");
@@ -368,8 +367,7 @@
   if (gxShareDir) locations.insert(locations.begin(), gxShareDir+std::string("/"));
   // Add 4)
